    <h1>Optical Test Engineer Training: CIE 1931</h1>

    <section class="section" id="introduction">
        <h2>Introduction to CIE 1931</h2>
        <p>
            The CIE 1931 color space is fundamental to modern color measurement and analysis. 
            It was developed by the International Commission on Illumination (CIE) in 1931 to 
            represent human color perception using standard observers.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="color-matching">
        <h2>Color Matching Functions</h2>
        <p>
            The CIE 1931 breaks down the spectrum into three primary components: X, Y, and Z. 
            Below is an example of how these components map to standard color wavelengths.
        </p>
